rComments: Not a very good prof. His writing is way to small and messy, and the structure of the lectures weren't always very clear. The assignments and group project was easy enough, but the exam very difficult. A large portion of the exam was true/false, where a wrong answer would give you -1, with the material based on obscure topics he barley covered.
Good lecturer, though seems he doesn't really like teaching.
very disorganized and confusing!

DISORGANIZED course. reuse same material from year to year,the lab material is definitely out of date (example as your to do AWS-ec2 python client) The first half of course is simply python and numpy tutorial that you can ABSOLUTELY learned by yourself.  5% quiz is all about reduction which he spends 30m in lecture. Take if only need for credit.

The prof himself is decent when he teaches, although he misunderstands the student's questions sometimes. But the biggest problem is how disorganized the course is.I had to send 3 to 4 emails to get a proper reply. The midterms were misprinted so we had to redo it. And the 2 pop quizzes are worth 10% in total. There's no portal so marks are emailed
lectures not well prepared. It seems he's not interested in teaching at all.
